===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ねこ}}
{{IPAfont|⟨neko<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/neko/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=ねこ|-}}. Cognate with {{cog|mvi|ja|にか|tr=nika|pos=Tarama dialect|cat}} via unknown Japonic substratum.
Many dialects with Tokyo type accent, including the standard Japanese in Tokyo, pronounce this word in <HL> tone, the same as the current Keihan type accent has, instead of <LH> as expected from the Heian Kyoto accent <LL>. The confusion seems to be due to it is from compound word origin.

One theory describes that this word is shortened from earlier {{ja-r|猫|linkto=|ねこま}} below, but this word's first appearance in literature is earlier than that.

First attested in ''Shin'yaku Kegonkyō Ongi Shiki'' (新訳華厳経音義私記), 794.
:{{RQ:Shin'yaku Kegonkyō Ongi Shiki}}
: {{ux|ja|猫狸 [...] ニ又漢云野貍、倭言上'''尼古'''、下多〻既|Cat and raccoon dog, [...] both of them are called {{m|ja||野貍|tr=yari}} in Chinese; the former is called {{m|ja||'''尼古'''|tr={{IPAfont|⟨neko<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → neko}} while the latter is called {{m|ja|狸|多〻既|tr={{IPAfont|⟨tatake<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → tatake}} in Japanese.}}

