===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ねこま}}

According to ''Wamyō Ruijushō'' (931–938), {{ja-r|猫|linkto=|ねこ}} above is short for this word.
: {{RQ:Wamyō Ruijushō|7|56}}
: {{lang|ja|猫: 野王案、猫、音苗、'''禰古麻'''、下總本有和名二字興河海抄引此合、本草和名同訓、或省云禰古、新撰字鏡、狸、禰古、按狸一名猫、見本草和名、似虎而小、熊捕鼠為糧}}

One theory describes the first mola <ne> is [[onomatopoeia]] for the sound a cat makes (cf. {{ja-r|にゃ}}; compare {{noncog|en|[[mew]], [[meow]]}}). The last two molae <ko<sub>1</sub>ma> can accord with {{ja-r|熊|くま|bear}} if it were from Proto-Japonic *kòmà, as a sense of "four-legged animal".
